import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
from typing import List, Dict, Optional

class DataProcessor:
def __init__(self, file_path: str):
self.file_path = file_path
self.data: Optional[pd.DataFrame] = None

def load_data(self) -> pd.DataFrame:
"" "
* @description loads the data file
! @return pd.DataFrame loaded data frame
"" "
try:
if self.file_path.endswith('.csv'):
self.data = pd.read_csv(self.file_path)
elif self.file_path.endswith('.xlsx'):
self.data = pd.read_excel(self.file_path)
else:
raise ValueError(" Unsupported File Format ")

print(f" Data loading successful: {self.data.shape}")
return self.data
except Exception as e:
print(f" Data loading failed: {e}")
raise

def clean_data(self) -> pd.DataFrame:
"" "
* @description Clean up data, delete duplicate lines and handle missing values
! @return pd.DataFrame The data frame after cleaning
"" "
if self.data is None:
raise ValueError(" Please load data first ")

# Delete duplicate lines
self.data.drop_duplicates(inplace=True)

# Handle Missing values
self.data.fillna(self.data.mean(), inplace=True)

return self.data

def get_summary(self) -> Dict[str, any]:
"" "
* @description Obtain data summary statistics information
! @return Dict[str, any] data digest dictionary
"" "
if self.data is None:
return {}

return {
'rows': len(self.data),
'columns': len(self.data.columns),
'missing_values': self.data.isnull().sum().sum(),
'dtypes': self.data.dtypes.to_dict()
}

if __name__ == "__main__":
processor = DataProcessor("data.csv")
processor.load_data()
processor.clean_data()
print(processor.get_summary())
